HEADWORD: Diurnation
<hw>Di`ur*na"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Continuance during the day.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The condition of sleeping or
becoming dormant by day, as is the case of the bats.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Diuturnal</ent>⟦br⟧
